<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
    <style>

      body {
        font-family: "Arial", sans-serif;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background-image: url("/img/space-background.jpg");
        background-size: cover;
        color: #fff;
      }

      main {
        height: 100%;
      }

      .stars-container {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-evenly;
        align-items: center;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      .star {
        width: 150px;
        height: 150px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        margin: 10px;
        background-size: cover;
        background-position: center;
        transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        cursor: pointer;
      }

      .star:hover {
        transform: scale(1.1);
      }

      .yellow-dwarf {
        background-image: url("/img/yellow-dwarf.jpg");
      }

      .red-giant {
        background-image: url("/img/red-giant.jpg");
      }

      .blue-supergiant {
        background-image: url("/img/blue-supergiant.jpg");
      }

      .white-dwarf {
        background-image: url("/img/white-dwarf.jpg");
      }

      .neutron-star {
        background-image: url("/img/neutron-star.jpg");
      }

      .black-hole {
        background-image: url("/img/black-hole.jpg");
      }

      .names {
        margin-top: 3.25rem;
        color: white;
        text-shadow: black .125rem .125rem;
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        font-size: 1.5625rem;
      }


      #descriptions {
        margin-top: 20px;
        color: white;
        text-shadow: black .125rem .125rem;
        backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
        font-size: 1.5625rem;
      }
    </style>
    <title>Galactic Explorer - Stars</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header>
      <h1>Galactic Explorer</h1>
      <nav>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/index">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="/stars">Stars</a></li>
          <li><a href="/planets">Planets</a></li>
          <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
          <li><a href="/login">Login</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <h2>Stars Page</h2>
      <div class="stars-container">
        <div class="star yellow-dwarf">
          <p class="names">Yellow Dwarf</p>
        </div>
        <div class="star red-giant">
          <p class="names">Red Giant</p>
        </div>
        <div class="star blue-supergiant">
          <p class="names">Blue Super Giant</p>
        </div>
        <div class="star white-dwarf">
          <p class="names">White Dwarf</p>
        </div>
        <div class="star neutron-star">
          <p class="names">Neutron Star</p>
        </div>
        <div class="star black-hole">
            <p class="names">Black Hole</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p id="descriptions">
        Stars come in various types, each with its unique characteristics.
        Yellow dwarf stars, like our Sun, are common and stable. Red giant stars
        expand as they age, while blue supergiants are massive and luminous.
        White dwarf stars are the remnants of smaller stars, and neutron stars
        are incredibly dense. Black holes have gravitational forces so strong
        that nothing, not even light, can escape them.
      </p>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <p>&copy; 2023 Galactic Explorer</p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
